[b]MA Regime Bands[/b] classifies the current market regime using multi-moving-average alignment and overlays ATR-based stop bands that reflect both trend direction and volatility.

[b]What it does[/b]

Three moving averages (configurable type and length) are evaluated together: their relative alignment determines the regime classification. ATR-based bands are drawn around the regime to give a dynamic stop and trend-continuation reference directly on the price chart.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Three configurable MAs[/b] — Default 21 / 55 / 89; supports SMA, EMA, DEMA, TEMA, JMA
[*][b]Regime classification[/b] — Bull, Bear, or Neutral based on MA stack alignment
[*][b]ATR-based stop bands[/b] — Dynamic bands rendered as an overlay around the regime
[*][b]Trend-strength gate[/b] — Regimes only trigger when the MA spread normalized by ATR exceeds a configurable minimum (Off / By MA Type / Auto normalization)
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]
All alerts fire only on confirmed bar close by default (configurable via "Alerts only on bar close" toggle).
[list]
[*][b]Bull Regime[/b] — MA stack flips to bullish alignment
[*][b]Bear Regime[/b] — MA stack flips to bearish alignment
[*][b]Neutral/Transition[/b] — regime exits bull or bear into neutral
[/list]

